INSERT INTO `wde_blog` VALUES (1,'Health','','WHY YOU SHOULD PRACTICE YOGA IN YOUR DAILY LIFE','why-you-should-practice-yoga-in-your-daily-life','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Yoga is adopted by many people not only as a way to keep fit, but as a true lifestyle as it produces changes in our body at multiple levels. A daily practice of gentle yoga feeds the metabolic system and helps rebuild our silhouette, eliminating fatty tissues and stimulating the formation of new muscle mass.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;One of the first positive changes that are perceived when starting to practice yoga is the increase in flexibility, very important because, among other things, it helps prevent injuries. It is likely that at first, the body is rigid, which is perceived more clearly in the torsions but with constancy, these positions are the best allies to increase flexibility.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;As you gain adherence to your yoga practice, you will notice that the aches and pains caused by an incorrect body posture (typical of daily life) such as back pain can also be relieved.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;It also establishes a unique synergy of body and respiratory work that is perfect when your reserves are running out thanks to those agitated busy days. It helps us to:&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&bull; Improve flexibility, strength, and posture.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Increase the energy level.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Reduce the level of stress.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; More concentration and fluidity of thought.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Longevity.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Yoga is the science of balanced life and the path to wisdom and abundance, as it has the ability to unite the body, mind, and spirit, the union between individual consciousness and universal consciousness. It combines aspects of cardio, calisthenics, functional training and strength training all in one.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Without a doubt, adopting yoga as a lifestyle will be really positive. All aspects of our life will be pleasantly rewarded.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','WHY YOU SHOULD PRACTICE YOGA IN YOUR DAILY LIFE','Yoga is adopted by many people not only as a way to keep fit, but as a true lifestyle as it produces changes in our body','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:18:58',0,'english',0),(2,'Health','','THE VALUE OF IMPECCABLE DENTAL HEALTH','the-value-of-impeccable-dental-health','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Maintaining proper oral hygiene can help prevent health problems. A healthy lifestyle and carry out simple oral hygiene every day will allow us to enjoy healthy teeth and gums. To do this, we must take into account both the recommendations of the specialists and a few simple steps for proper oral hygiene. We must clean every day in addition to the teeth, tongue, gums, palate and inside the cheeks. Performing this cleaning process periodically minimizes tartar, as well as preventing its formation. It also guarantees the integrity of the teeth and the good health of the gums, which should always be firm and pink and should not bleed during brushing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Keys to proper oral health: &lt;br /&gt; 1. Brush your teeth carefully.&lt;br /&gt; Ideally, do it after each meal, but if there is no other option, you should at least brush your teeth before going to sleep. The operation should last between two and three minutes and be done with small circular movements back and forth.&lt;br /&gt; 2. Clean the interdental spaces.&lt;br /&gt; If there is enough space, an interproximal brush or floss should be used. Both should be used at least once a day, preferably at night, in order to ensure the cleanliness of the side faces of the teeth and that there is no food left between them.&lt;br /&gt; 3. Do not forget the gums.&lt;br /&gt; And neither of the tongue, the palate and the inside of the cheeks, because they also accumulate the bacteria that can cause different dental disorders.&lt;br /&gt; 4. Renew your brush every two weeks or when the bristles start to look worn out. These, on the other hand, are preferable to be soft to prevent damage to tooth enamel.&lt;br /&gt; 5. Go to your dentist regularly.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Because not even deep brushing completely eliminates dental plaque, mouth cleanings are recommended every six to twelve months. Likewise, you should check your teeth at least once a year. Specialists recommend professional oral hygiene -prophylaxis- every 4 or 6 months.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Additionally, minimize the intake of carbohydrates in your diet, avoid sweets and sugary drinks. Limit pecking between meals. Use mouthwashes to prevent the formation of bacterial plaque and provide fresh breath. Eradicate customs such as opening bottles, cutting heat with your teeth or chewing ice. The teeth can splinter and even, if there is a fracture, damage the nerve and compromise the stability of the tooth.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Finally, saliva plays a fundamental role in our dental health. Not only does it collaborate in the chewing and swallowing process, but it regulates the pH level of the mouth and prevents carious formations. To achieve optimal levels of segregation, it is advisable to stay hydrated and drink plenty of water - at least 1.5 liters a day.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','THE VALUE OF IMPECCABLE DENTAL HEALTH','Maintaining proper oral hygiene can help prevent health problems. A healthy lifestyle and carry out simple oral hygiene every day will allow us to enjoy health','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:19:24',0,'english',0),(3,'Health','','THE IMPORTANCE OF ADEQUATE HYDRATION FOR GOOD HEALTH','the-importance-of-adequate-hydration-for-good-heal','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Water is a source of life and is essential for the hydration of our bodies. It is the moisturizer par excellence, the healthiest and the most natural. So good hydration is important for our physical and mental health. Our brain is made up of 90% water, 83% blood, 75% muscle mass, and 22% bones, so we can say that water is one of the main components of the human body.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;We must learn to listen to the body when it asks for water. To understand that the sensation of thirst is the way you have to ask us for liquid. Maintaining an adequate level of hydration is essential for survival, health, physical and mental performance. Water should even be ingested, without the absence of thirst.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; In order to hydrate our body, it is necessary to consume at least 2 liters of water a day, but other foods, such as fruit, vegetables or drinks such as infusions, soft drinks, juices, dairy, also provide us with the water we need.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; One of the benefits of staying hydrated is that this facilitates the oxygenation of brain cells and allows the brain to remain active to perform all its actions. Dehydration in the brain can cause serious health problems. With good hydration, the elimination of accumulated toxins is facilitated. Thanks to this, an adequate metabolic function is obtained.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Water rehydrates your skin. One of the main benefits and reasons why you should drink water is that it is your greatest ally to show and have a shiny skin, especially if you are very exposed to the sun or exercise. It lubricates joints. In addition to being one of the best skin rehydrators, water consumption lubricates your joints and prevents wear and cramps when you exercise or activities that require a lot of physical effort. It prevents acne. Water consumption is one of the best allies when it comes to taking care of your face and complexion as it prevents the appearance of acne by maintaining the correct amount of fat on the skin.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; In addition to being of great benefit and importance for your skin, water has other impacts on your overall health such as the brain, organs, stomach, care, and weight control, etc. It is only important to keep in mind that you should consume the amount of water your body needs, so there is no exact recipe for how much in liters you should consume daily, but always try to make it very often.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; It is important to maintain adequate hydration, especially in hot weather that more water is lost due to sweating. Remember: hydration is important throughout the year. Don&#039;t neglect it!&nbsp;&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','THE IMPORTANCE OF ADEQUATE HYDRATION FOR GOOD HEALTH','Water is a source of life and is essential for the hydration of our bodies. It is the moisturizer par excellence, the healthiest and the most natural. So good','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:19:48',0,'english',0),(4,'Health','','SELF-CARE: FOUNDATION OF WELLNESS','selfcare-foundation-of-wellness','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Why is self-care so important? The answer is quite simple: because it is free health insurance. The only cost you have is the time you dedicate. Self-care prevents diseases, immunizes you, and protects your health, both physically and psychologically. The challenge in today&#039;s society is for the individual to move from a passive attitude, from a care recipient to an active or proactive one, from the search for well-being and responsibility for their own health.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;When we prioritize work, domestic or interpersonal objectives for too long, leaving aside our personal well-being, our body begins to warn us that we are overloading ourselves. It does so through symptoms of physical discomfort that are common in people with stress, such as:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;- Headaches or brain fog.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;- Nausea, diarrhea, gas.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;- Muscle pain, muscle spasms, weakness.&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p2&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;- Palpitations, choking sensation.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Among the practices for self-care are: adequate feeding to the needs, hygienic measures, stress management, skills to establish social relationships and solve interpersonal problems, exercise and physical activity required, ability to adapt the consumption of medications, monitoring of prescriptions of health, safe sexual behaviors, recreation and free time management, dialogue, favorable adaptations to changes in context, information search and management of different signs and symptoms in diseases. Family, school, social environment and health personnel can favor and empower people for greater and better self-care.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; One of the most recurring barriers to postpone self-care activities is that of automatic negative thoughts, that is, thoughts that slip into our head and that make us feel bad, normally of guilt.&lt;br /&gt; The essence of self-care is the individual&#039;s control over their health, empowerment, and the right of all people, which should be encouraged to the fullest until the end of life. Keep this habit in the long term, not when you need it but constantly, so you don&#039;t have to need it in the future.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','SELF-CARE: FOUNDATION OF WELLNESS','Why is self-care so important? The answer is quite simple: because it is free health insurance. The only cost you have is the time you dedicate. Self-care prev','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:20:41',0,'english',0),(5,'Fitness','','HOW TO HAVE A BETTER ATTITUDE TOWARDS FITNESS','how-to-have-a-better-attitude-towards-fitness','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Exercising routinely is a task that not everyone manages to maintain over time. Phrases like &quot;I start on Monday&quot; are repeated week by week, but the exercises are buried under increasingly creative excuses.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Stop postponing exercise. It is not Monday, it is not the first of the month, nor at the beginning of the year. Is now! Take advantage that you are reading this article to start your exercises. It doesn&#039;t matter if you do squats in front of the TV, or you go to a huge gym. The important thing is that you start now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Do exercises early. If you think you do not have time, or when you have finished your daily duties it is too late. Then we recommend that you do your exercise routine first thing in the morning, it is very difficult to give up since it will be the first thing you do during the day. At dawn, there are fewer distractions, more concentration and a lot of energy.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Follow these tips for a better attitude towards exercise:&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Do not see the exercise as a penance, but as a distraction.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Do not stop your exercise before the first pain you feel at the muscular level since this is natural at the beginning.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; If you are one of the people who need someone to motivate you, seek help from a partner or an instructor.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Avoid prolonged breaks, this loses work effectiveness and produces cooling in the body.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Always look at your goals as something attainable and what you will achieve.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Remember that you always have to start from scratch and that everyone has done it.&lt;br /&gt; &bull; Concentration is fundamental: just as we focus on our work or studies, exercise needs concentration.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; There are no excuses. It doesn&#039;t matter if the day is cloudy or rainy, you can exercise indoors. If you had a lot of work, the exercise fills you with energy and helps you sleep better. If you feel depressed, exercise will secrete the hormones of happiness that will make you feel good. If your knees hurt, exercise your arms, if you broke your arm, work your legs. There is nothing that prevents you from starting right now.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','HOW TO HAVE A BETTER ATTITUDE TOWARDS FITNESS','Exercising routinely is a task that not everyone manages to maintain over time. Phrases like &quot;I start on Monday&quot; are repeated week by week, but the ex','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:21:08',0,'english',0),(6,'Health','','STEPS THAT LEAD TO A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE','-steps-that-lead-to-a-healthy-lifestyle','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;The World Health Organization published in its most recent report the diseases that cause the most deaths in the world, all linked to unhealthy lifestyles: Cardiovascular diseases 17.7 million deaths per year; Cancer of all kind 8.8 million deaths a year; Respiratory diseases 3.9 million deaths per year; Diabetes 1.6 million deaths a year.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The good news is that we can avoid entering these statistics just by changing some bad habits.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Exercise. Performing physical activity is not only good for weight loss, but it also improves heart and lung capacity, helps prevent and even treat chronic diseases (such as hypertension, cancer, and depression) and lowers cholesterol. In addition, it improves the quality of sleep and has a regulatory effect of stress, so it reduces anxiety and stabilizes mood.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Sleep well. Sleep is an indicator of health. Some cardiovascular, respiratory and metabolic diseases are linked to sleep quality. Try to sleep for the necessary time, but remember that to stay healthy we need both quantity and quality.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Reduce stress. A constant state of stress causes us to lose muscle mass and accumulate more fat; It raises blood pressure, increases blood cholesterol and lowers levels of good cholesterol or HDL. This translates into body weight gain and, therefore, an increased risk of chronic non-communicable diseases. Fight stress by getting a massage, practicing yoga or meditation.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Periodic medical checkup. To prevent and to heal you. The doctor can guide you to modify risk factors for new conditions. Most diseases can be cured if they are detected in time. Don&#039;t forget to have a checkup.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Living in society. Psychosocial well-being is part of health. Do recreational activities that allow you to have fun and distract yourself. Visit different places, take a walk through nature and take the opportunity to pamper yourself with those you love most. Remember that health is not the absence of diseases, but the perfect balance between your body, mind, and spirit.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Nutritional changes. You can start with small changes that will have great effects on your health. Change processed meat, such as cold meats and fatty red meats, for lean and unprocessed meat, for poultry and even better, fatty fish such as salmon. Always serve 3-ounce servings and complement your plate with fruits and vegetables, whole grains, low-fat dairy and small amounts of healthy fat, such as olive oil.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Remember that it is not enough to want to have a healthy lifestyle to prevent and combat body diseases, it is also necessary to take care of mental health and the new challenges of modern life.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','STEPS THAT LEAD TO A HEALTHY LIFESTYLE','The World Health Organization published in its most recent report the diseases that cause the most deaths in the world, all linked to unhealthy lifestyles: Car','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:21:23',0,'english',0),(7,'Beauty','','HOW TO MAKE YOUR TAN LAST LONGER','how-to-make-your-tan-last-longer','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;To keep the tan longer it is also important to take care of the skin after a day at the beach or pool. UV radiation causes a great loss of water and, therefore, can dry the skin. Follow these tips and do not let the return of the holidays or the arrival of autumn turn off your tan.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Exfoliate. Tanned skin thickens as a natural defense, which causes it to appear dry and cracked. If we exfoliate it regularly, we will keep the skin dry and dead at bay and the deeper cells may show better. Exfoliating the skin will not make the tan go faster, but it will make your skin brighter and in better condition after sun exposure.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Take vitamin D. One of the vitamins that will best help you absorb the sun&#039;s rays without damaging your skin and get a beautiful tan tone is vitamin D. Therefore, it is important that in this new stage you try to take more vitamin D through of your diet you can find it in foods such as nuts, whole grains, legumes, etc.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;After sun lotion. If you have become accustomed to using lotion after sun exposure during the summer to relieve your skin from excess heat and soothe it, you can continue using it later even more. The after sun properties are very good and will allow your tan to last longer. These products usually have moisturizing and soothing assets and many, in addition, include ingredients that will help you keep the tan longer conceived precisely to nourish and repair the skin after sunbathing.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Good nutrition. Another of the tricks to get a sunless tan or, at least, to accelerate it as much as possible when you do not have too much time, is to have an adequate diet. Try to keep your diet always rich in beta-carotene that helps your melanin to activate, as well as nourish yourself well with foods with vitamins C and E and Omega 3. You know, a lot of red fruit, citrus fruits, avocado and blue fish, among others delicacies.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Hydration. When it comes to getting a tan that respects your skin, you can&#039;t miss a good dose of hydration. To preserve the tan and combat the dry effect of the sun it is very important to stay hydrated inside (drink water and natural juices) and outside (skin moisturizers). Apply any normal moisturizer you use after showering every time you feel dry skin. In addition to the normal moisturizer, opt for post-tanning creams, such as aloe vera, will improve its elasticity, and prevent premature appearance of wrinkles on the face and stretch marks on the body.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Now there are no excuses to wear a golden skin also in winter.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','HOW TO MAKE YOUR TAN LAST LONGER','To keep the tan longer it is also important to take care of the skin after a day at the beach or pool. UV radiation causes a great loss of water and, therefore','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:21:40',0,'english',0),(8,'Health','','WAYS TO RELIEVE STRESS','ways-to-relieve-stress','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Stress is a modern disease. Everyone complains of suffering from it and many other diseases are caused by it. When some situations reach us, sometimes we feel so anxious that we try to reduce it on our own such as self-medication, but in the long run this can be detrimental to our health.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; What can we do to relieve it and enjoy life more? It is best to follow relaxation techniques for the body and mind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Massages go beyond being a beauty treatment. A relaxing massage has proven to be an effective tool to relieve stress. Massage is a powerful treatment that also helps us replenish the innate reserves of vital energy. &lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Another effective technique to manage stress is yoga, a discipline that combines a series of gentle movements and static poses with deep breathing. Most yoga classes end with relaxation poses, and there are certain types of yoga that emphasize slow and steady movements, breathing exercises and gentle stretching that are very beneficial for stress relief. Other properties include increased flexibility, strength, balance, and endurance.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Listening to or playing music is a good stress reliever because it can provide a mental distraction, reduce muscle tension and decrease stress hormones. Turn up the volume and let your mind get absorbed by the music.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Exercising regularly is one of the best ways to manage stress. When you exercise your body releases substances that make you feel better emotionally. In addition, you release muscle tension, among other benefits, it is an antidote against worries and stress.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Having a diary is another option to eliminate anxiety and stress. When you have the practice of writing before bedtime, you begin to be more aware of your emotions (negative and positive) and identify why you are feeling this way, you will have a better vision of how to solve your problems and feel less anxiety.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Finally, if you have a bad day and growl at people, you add hostility to the environment and raise the level of general stress. Make the effort to smile and be kind, you will reduce the anxiety of others, and above all, yours.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','WAYS TO RELIEVE STRESS','Stress is a modern disease. Everyone complains of suffering from it and many other diseases are caused by it. When some situations reach us, sometimes we feel','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:25:37',0,'english',0),(9,'Health','','HOW TO REST WELL AT NIGHT','how-to-rest-well-at-night','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;People need to sleep a third of the day, that is, about 8 hours or so, although there is no clear rule. In fact, there are people who with 6 hours can lead a perfectly normal day and not feel tired and yes at full capacity, while others instead need to sleep 10 hours. However, regardless of what we need to sleep, the truth is that there are a number of hours necessary for the body to function properly.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Despite advances in science within the health sector, sleep disturbances continue to accompany us in full 2019. To date, they have been associated with aspects such as the development of obesity, dementias, biological suicide and even death early.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; It is well known that the routine of human beings has changed by leaps and bounds together with technological development. The way and the speed at which we live are totally different from that of our grandparents, and this has played a big impact on our health as we can see in recent years cases of dementia have multiplied.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The consequences are not only reflected in neurological deficiencies (less attention, function and long-term memory), they are also related to weight gain processes. Since, with deprivation, restriction or lack of sleep, more appetite, cravings and greater caloric intake by the affected is detected.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; For all this, taking care of sleep is one of the most important things we can do to take care of our health. To make each day safe and productive, follow certain steps to make sure you sleep well regularly.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; To sleep well it is important to follow good habits:&nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;- Go to sleep at the same time each night, get up at the same time each morning.&lt;br /&gt; -Avoid naps after 3 p.m. &lt;br /&gt; -Stay away from caffeine and alcohol at night.&lt;br /&gt; -Avoid nicotine completely.&lt;br /&gt; -Exercise regularly, but avoid doing it 2 to 3 hours before bedtime.&lt;br /&gt; -Do not eat a heavy meal at night, opt for a light snack.&lt;br /&gt; -Make your bedroom comfortable, dark, quiet and not too warm or too cold.&lt;br /&gt; -Follow a routine that helps you relax before bedtime (for example, reading or listening to music).&lt;br /&gt; -Do not rest in bed awake. If you cannot fall asleep after 20 minutes, do something calming until you are sleepy, such as reading or listening to soft music.&lt;br /&gt; -Consult a doctor if you continue to have trouble sleeping.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Carry out these good practices and they will allow you to sleep better.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','HOW TO REST WELL AT NIGHT','People need to sleep a third of the day, that is, about 8 hours or so, although there is no clear rule. In fact, there are people who with 6 hours can lead a p','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:23:01',0,'english',0),(10,'Fitness','','WORKOUT TIPS FOR BEGINNERS','workout-tips-for-beginner','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;In the beginner stage, improving motor learning and coordination, increasing work capacity, volume tolerance, and recovery and advancing in the construction of a basic level of strength, muscle and endurance are really important goals. In fact, reaching them will allow you to achieve other goals such as muscle building, strength, tone, fat loss, improved health or fitness level. All of them will begin to happen quickly as a side effect.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; If you want to achieve results in your physical training you must have constancy and willpower. These results will not come overnight, much less if you have always led a sedentary life. Start training three days a week, this will allow you to always have a recovery day. The exercise for beginners always involves an extra effort to the body.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;&lt;br /&gt; Start with something very soft. A bike ride, walking with your partner or just listening to music, running in the morning and if you have a knee injury, use an elliptical. Always start with a brief warm-up of about 5 to 10 minutes of low-intensity aerobics, because that way you can raise your muscle temperature and also the cardiorespiratory rhythm.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Whether you&#039;re doing cardio or lifting weights, it&#039;s easy to hurt yourself if your training or technique is wrong. If the routine is causing you pain, stop immediately and talk to an expert and find advice on how to improve your training technique.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; It is always a good idea to receive advice from a doctor or a physiotherapist before making major changes in your lifestyle, such as starting a training plan, especially if you are over 45 years old, suffer from a chronic illness, or were injured in the past.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Do not wear out from the beginning. Keep in mind that the results come with time and consistency and you will not find them in a supplement. Therefore, do not fool yourself and do not spend money before organizing your physical training and your balanced diet to maintain a good diet. Two fundamental points to reach success.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Do not forget to keep your motivation, mix the workouts, join a gym or a group of friends for sports, but leave sedentary life behind.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','WORKOUT TIPS FOR BEGINNER','In the beginner stage, improving motor learning and coordination, increasing work capacity, volume tolerance, and recovery and advancing in the construction of','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-12-20 22:06:32',0,'english',0),(11,'Health','','IMPROVING YOUR MENTAL HEALTH','improving-your-mental-health','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Emotional well-being is as important as physical health. So much so, that when our lies suffer, our body begins to fail.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Mental health is the state of equilibrium between a person and their socio-cultural environment that guarantees their labor, intellectual and relationship participation to achieve well-being and quality of life. Since it is the observation of the behavior of a person in their daily life the main way of knowing the state of their mental health in aspects such as, the management of their conflicts, fears and capacities, their competences and responsibilities, the maintenance of their own needs, the way he faces his own tensions, his interpersonal relationships and the way he directs an independent life, the concept is necessarily subjective and culturally determined.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Do not be afraid to recognize that you need to improve your mental health. This is not synonymous with madness, nor disturbance, but it is a much broader field than traditionally thought.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The development of programs based on strengthening self-esteem and acceptable social behaviors, as well as the application of strategies for social integration, conflict resolution and emotion management, especially stress, can help maintain optimal mental health.&lt;span class=&quot;Apple-converted-space&quot;&gt;&nbsp; &lt;/span&gt;Here are some suggestions that will help you improve the functioning of your brain and enhance your mental capacity:&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Stay active, there is nothing better than walking outdoors surrounded by nature. According to scientific studies, when walking outdoors, the brain generates more vitality and endorphins and you get to think more clearly.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Rest, lavender oil helps improve the quality of your sleep and fights insomnia.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Increase self-confidence: recognize who we are and the strengths and weaknesses that characterize us, to create a version of ourselves with which we feel more comfortable.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;Express your emotions and worries. When you are sad, worried or stressed, share those feelings with the people you trust, you will see that it will suit you and your mental state will improve.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Do new things like starting a new professional challenge or making plans related to leisure. Think about vital changes, desires or aspirations, you will know what can bring you happy. Find it and work on it.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; As you can see, improving mental health is within the reach of anyone. The only requirement is to organize your agenda and set aside time for yourself.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','IMPROVING YOUR MENTAL HEALTH','Emotional well-being is as important as physical health. So much so, that when our lies suffer, our body begins to fail.  Mental health is the state of equilib','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:23:57',0,'english',0),(12,'Fitness','','THE BEST NUTRITION TIPS FOR ATHLETES','the-best-nutrition-tips-for-athletes','&lt;p&gt;&lt;/p&gt;\r\n&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;s1&quot;&gt;The process to improve the performance of athletes is a sports training that leads to the breakdown of muscle fibers, which with proper nutrition regenerate and contribute to the increase of muscle mass. But for this procedure to be carried out correctly, nutrition is a primary factor for anyone who wants or practices a sport.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; The main component in building muscles is the amount of protein consumed. They can be found, mainly, in meats such as beef, chicken or fish; however, many vegetables also have a large amount of protein that, being less qualified than animal protein, are also very easy to find as chickpeas, lentils or legumes.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; 30 minutes before starting the routine, depending on the type and duration of the exercise you do, it is advisable to eat a small snack and drink some water 30 minutes before physical activity. You can opt for example a granola bar, a large banana, fig bars.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Always have breakfast daily. The most appropriate is to have a varied breakfast. It could be a yogurt, flax, whey protein and frozen strawberries smoothie, or a whole-grain toast, peanut butter, and a banana. A variety of cereals is another option.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; Water consumption is essential because it helps metabolism, cleanses the body, oxygenates the blood and mainly keeps the body and the muscular system hydrated. The good habit of water consumption is part of the diet of every good athlete.&lt;br /&gt; &lt;br /&gt; In short, we are what we eat and the better we do it, the better results we will get. Going with the nutritionist represents a very good option because under the particular conditions that you may have as your body mass, habits and future goals, a specific diet will be designed.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;','','THE BEST NUTRITION TIPS FOR ATHLETES','The process to improve the performance of athletes is a sports training that leads to the breakdown of muscle fibers, which with proper nutrition regenerate an','',1,0,0,0,1,'2019-11-21 19:00:00','2019-11-21 22:24:25',0,'english',0),(13,'Beauty','29','5 WAYS TO MAINTAIN YOUR LIPOSUCTION RESULTS','13-','&amp;lt;grammarly-extension class=&amp;quot;_1KJtL&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;position: absolute; top: 0px; left: -1px; pointer-events: none;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div data-grammarly-part=&amp;quot;highlights&amp;quot; class=&amp;quot;u_fNK&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div style=&amp;quot;box-sizing: content-box; top: 0px; left: 1px; width: 797px; height: 499px; position: relative; pointer-events: none; overflow: hidden; border: 0px; border-radius: 0px; padding: 0px; margin: 0px;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div style=&amp;quot;position: absolute; top: 0px; left: 0px;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div style=&amp;quot;height: 1928px; width: 2717px;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div class=&amp;quot;_3F-Wk _3mEyK _2Qe2S&amp;quot; style=&amp;quot;top: 553px; left: 210px; width: 49px; height: 15px;&amp;quot;&amp;gt;&amp;lt;/div&amp;gt;&amp;lt;div clas